      "name": "Microservice Architecture",
      "abstract": "Microservices can improve independent evolution and scaling but add network, data, deployment, observability and organizational complexity.",
      "description": "Microservice architecture structures a software system as independently deployable services aligned with bounded capabilities and communicating through explicit contracts.",
